The Archimedes Sphere is a tiny sized mechanical device that effectively allows for multiple items and their uses to be combined together through flavor text.

Roughly twice the size of a baseball, Archimedes Spheres are made up of metal plates of varying material, with 10 holes inset into its surface. By inserting their fingers into the openings, a being can activate and manipulate the sphere for one of its several uses.

Around the center of the sphere are 4 eyelets, each of which has a thin braided metal cable, about 6 inches long, that wrap up into a thick cable that acts as a handle. All together about 1.5 feet in length.

------

Note: for each of these uses, you must have the original item, and must take 1 hour of uninterrupted time to integrate the items together. Once integrated, the items can effectively be considered one.

+++ Uses:
**Writing:** This is the original primary use of the device. It is an artificer wizard's spellbook, specially designed for recording information through a series of whirs, clicks, and hums that can only be felt when manipulating the sphere. This writing ability can be used for anything from a wizards spellbook, to a standard diary. As long as the item is used via the physical transcription of information, it can be replaced with this ability. (Because this is a tactile method of reading/writing, it cannot effect or be effected by things that must be visually read such as illusory script. Similarly, a creature does not require eyesight or hearing to read or write information using this device, they only need to understand the simple, morse code-like language that the sphere uses. A creature with 10+ int can learn this language after a weeks worth of working with the device. 15+ int can learn it in 3 days, and 18+ int can learn it in a single day.)

